                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13827358" author="mishail" created="Wed, 20 Nov 2013 05:27:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching the patch to close the stream to unlock the file&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13827634" author="yukim" created="Wed, 20 Nov 2013 13:24:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&apos;finally&apos; block does close iStream, so I think there isn&apos;t a problem in current code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13827636" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 20 Nov 2013 13:26:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM; committed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Didn&apos;t see Yuki&apos;s comment.  The problem is that the catch block runs before the finally, so it tries to delete before the close, which works on linux but not windows.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
